==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semiprecious
<hw>Sem`i*pre"cious</hw> <pr>(s⟦ecr⟧m`⟦icr⟧*pr⟦ecr⟧sh"⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Somewhat precious; <as>as, <ex>semiprecious</ex>
stones or metals</as>. Used mostly of gemstones used in jewelry, such as
amethyst, garnet, or iolite, which are sufficiently rare to have
commercial value, but are not considered as <contr>precious</contr>, as
are the diamond, emerald, and ruby.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

